    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Front Cover, Cooling System, and Related
        Components - Installation - Front Crankcase Cover
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s09.4.2" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Front Crankcase Cover</title>
        <figure id="f3450009031" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD06/D0628A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Liquid gasket applications</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, install gasket and cover within 5 minutes of Liquid Gasket (RTV)
                    application to inhibit the formation of a skin and ensure a leak proof joint.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_200.xml" xrefid="s09.t3">Liquid Gasket (RTV)</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s09.t3"/>
                to joining surfaces of upper crankcase and lower crankcase assemblies.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a new front cover gasket on crankcase.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450009032" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM05/M05125.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="532px"
                     scalefitheight="408px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Front crankcase cover bolts</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 75 bolt (7)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 45 bolt (10)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, use a suitable lifting device and get help when removing,
                    lowering, and installing the front cover.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Install front crankcase cover with oil pump assembly in place for proper gerotor alignment.</para>
            </note>
            <note>
                <para>It may be necessary to manually turn oil pump gerotors, so they index onto crankshaft correctly.
                </para>
            </note>
            <note>
                <para>Support front crankcase cover while installing bolts.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install front crankcase cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install seven M8&#160;x&#160;75 bolts and 10 M8&#160;x&#160;45 bolts. Tighten bolts to
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_199.xml" xrefid="s09.t2">special torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s09.t2"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
